cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a method for improving the sample complexity of model-based reinforcement learning by learning a synthesized model that matches the distributions of multi-step rollouts sampled from the synthesized model and the real ones via WGAN. This involves techniques from machine learning (supervised learning, WGAN) and robotics (reinforcement learning, dynamic models), which are covered by the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.SY. Additionally, the paper uses visual inputs in some of the experiments, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV.
